abstract: He won’t be on the debate stage next week. But he says his campaign continues, “debate or not.”
snippet: He won’t be on the debate stage next week. But he says his campaign continues, “debate or not.”
lead_paragraph: In less than six hours, we will know who’s officially made the cut for next week’s Democratic primary debate.

abstract: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
snippet: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.

headline_print_headline: Poll Shows Impeachment Hearings Had Little Sway on Wisconsin Voters

abstract: Cory Booker will remain in the Democratic presidential race even though he does not expect to qualify for next week's primary debate, he announced Thursday, after a burst of fundraising support has given him the resources he needs to continue his bid.
snippet: Cory Booker will remain in the Democratic presidential race even though he does not expect to qualify for next week's primary debate, he announced Thursday, after a burst of fundraising support has given him the resources he needs to continue his ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Cory Booker will remain in the Democratic presidential race even though he does not expect to qualify for next week's primary debate, he announced Thursday, after a burst of fundraising support has given him the resources he needs to continue his bid.
headline_main: Cory Booker Expects to Miss Next Debate but Won't Drop Out
headline_print_headline: Cory Booker Expects to Miss Next Debate but Won't Drop Out

abstract: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
snippet: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
headline_main: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate

abstract: A library media specialist tells us about the ways her school — from the science department to the principal’s office — teaches with The Times.
snippet: A library media specialist tells us about the ways her school — from the science department to the principal’s office — teaches with The Times.
lead_paragraph: Often, teachers will write to us about one or two ways they’ve used The Times in their classrooms. But this idea, submitted by Susan Shatford, a library media specialist at Marblehead High School in Marblehead, Mass., is different.

abstract: Millions of people have a stake in corporate America through mutual funds. But you may be surprised by how those funds are voting on your behalf.

lead_paragraph: When somebody offers something for nothing, I don’t cheer. I reach in my pocket to see if my wallet is still there.

lead_paragraph: Among the millions of recent eviction cases researchers have begun to compile across the country, there are a startling number of modest sums. There are dozens of families in Texas evicted with money judgments — unpaid rent, late fees, court costs — totaling $516. There are multiple families in Cumberland County, N.C., who owed all of $301. There is a household in Providence, R.I., whose 2016 court record shows a debt of just $127.
